value.value: A coded value specifying the determination of the value, significance, or extent of an entity.
The date (and time) on which an assessment is completed.
Specifies whether an assessment is an estimate.
Specifies whether or not an entity is accessible for assessment or testing.
Specifies whether the entity is a starting point to which other things may be compared.
Specifies whether an entity is considered a biomarker.
A coded value specifying the name of the country in which the biologic entity is born.
Indicates the sequence of a biologic entity's birth in the family group.
The textual representation of the activity on a blinded participant or study subject (from the point of view of the study investigator).
A coded value specifying the roles of individuals who are masked for blinded studies.
The reemergence of duodenal carcinoma after a period of remission.
A coded value specifying the type of blinding that is used for the trial.
A coded value specifying the 3-dimensional spatial orientation of an entity.
A coded value specifying the anatomical grouping that consists of organs and organ subclasses that are together responsible for certain body functions.
A coded value specifying a group of animals presumably related by descent from common ancestors and visibly similar in most characteristics.
A coded value specifying a classification.
A coded value specifying the kind of cells found.
A coded value specifying the degree of cellular differentiation in a sample.
A character string that describes the certification or specific licensed credentials of the qualified entity.
A quantity of time that elapses between two repeating activities or events.
The rationale for why an entity or event is changed.
The reemergence of a hypopharyngeal malignant neoplasm after a period of remission.
A coded value specifying a modification.
A bibliographical reference in an acceptable format.
Specifies whether a finding or condition is clinically significant based on judgment.
A coded value specifying the form in which the entity is transmitted.
A coded value specifying the type of ancillary entity or event to the primary entity or event.
Specifies whether an event or activity must be completed prior to starting another activity.
A coded value specifying the state of being of an entity.
The coding system used for recording a state of being, such as a state of health.
A coded value specifying the degree of privacy applicable for the entity.
Specifies whether a person has authorized the use and disclosure of their private and/or confidential information.
The reemergence of a malignant neoplasm of the stomach after a period of remission.
A coded value specifying the anatomic site with which the entity has contact.
A coded value specifying the type of container cap.
Specifies whether the entity is enhanced by the use of a contrast agent.
A coded value specifying the relationship between the study control and an entity or event.
A coded value specifying the kind of comparison or comparator against which another entity is evaluated.
The date and time span specifying when an activity or event began and ended.
Specifies whether the life of an entity has ceased.
A coded value specifying the kind of reported problem with the product.
The time delay between two events.
A coded value specifying how something is to be conveyed.

A character string containing a formal language expression that specifies how attributes are, should be, or have been derived from input parameters associated with activity.
A coded value specifying a classification of a deviation.
A coded value specifying the defect or malfunction that occurred during use of the device.
The result or product of multiplying dimensions.
A coded value specifying the amount of disease present in a subject.
The sequence or position of a component in a list.
